<HL>
   Business Brief -- Sotheby's Holdings Inc.:
   Profit Rose 15%, Sales 26%
   During the First Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
05/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C8
</SO>
<CO>
   BID
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Sotheby's Holdings Inc. reported that first-quarter net
income rose 15% on strong buying in all collecting areas.
   The New York auction concern's net rose to $6 million, or
10 cents a share, from $5.2 million, or nine cents a share, a
year earlier. Sales grew 26% to $61.4 million from $48.9
million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Michael L. Ainslie, Sotheby's president, said that in the
first quarter, auction sales of $282.3 million were up 39%
from a year earlier, with strong buying in Old Master
paintings, jewelry, furniture and rare books.
   Sotheby's shares rose 50 cents Friday to close at $19.75 a
share in composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange.
</TEXT>
